HEADWORD: Anglo-Saxonism
<hw>An"glo-Sax"on*ism</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A characteristic of the Anglo-Saxon race; especially, a word or an
idiom of the Anglo-Saxon tongue.</def> <rj><au>M. Arnold.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The quality or sentiment of being Anglo-Saxon, or
English in its ethnological sense.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Angola</ent>⟦br⟧
